          <b><span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ἕδνον</span></b>  (<span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ϝέδνον</span>), only pl. <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ἕδνα,
            ἔεδνα</span>: (1) <span class="alpheios-lex-gloss">bridal gifts</span>, presented by the
          suitor to the father of the bride, as if to purchase her. —(2)
            <span class="alpheios-lex-gloss">dowry</span> of the bride, given to her by her father, <i><span class="en">Od. 1.277</span></i>.</div> <div class="alpheios-lex-footnotes en"> </div>
